(secondQuint)A Pilot Study to Evaluate the ROX Anastomotic Coupler System in Patients With Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease.

 Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease (COPD) is a chronic disease that leads to irreversible changes in the lung structure, but also to systemic changes in the body that can influence the severity of the disease.

 The irreversible changes to the lungs can be seen in limitations to the pulmonary function.

 The purpose of this clinical investigation is to evaluate the performance and efficacy of the ROX percutaneous Anastomotic Coupler System.

